What is a Transistor?
A transistor is a three-terminal device used for:
Amplification
Switching
Types of Transistors
1. BJT (Bipolar Junction Transistor)

Two types:

NPN
PNP
Terminals
Emitter (E) – releases charge carriers
Base (B) – controls the transistor
Collector (C) – collects charge carriers
Working (Simple Idea)
A small current at the base controls a large current between collector and emitter
 Like a control valve

2. FET (Field Effect Transistor)
Voltage-controlled device
Types: JFET, MOSFET
